FBIS3-11477 "drlat055_m_94009" FBIS-LAT-94-055 Document Type:Daily Report 21 Mar 1994 Brazil Foreign Ministry To Discuss UN Council Expansion With G-7 PY2203025594 Sao Paulo GAZETA MERCANTIL in Portuguese 21 Mar 94 p 5 PY2203025594 Sao Paulo GAZETA MERCANTIL Language: Portuguese Article Type:BFN [Article by Maria Helena Tachinardi from Brasilia] [Text] The Foreign Ministry will this week begin a series of contacts with industrialized countries, most of them members of the Group of Seven (G-7), to exchange ideas about expanding the UN Security Council and to find out how England, Italy, Sweden, Switzerland, Germany, France, Russian, Japan, the United States, and Canada view the possibility of granting Brazil a seat at the expanded UN Council. U.S. Vice President Al Gore will meet President Itamar Franco at 1900 on 21 March, when he will sign with Foreign Minister Celso Amorim a protocol modifying the current framework agreement of scientific and technological cooperation between the two countries, thus making relations in this area more complex and aimed at high technology sectors.
